<paragraph blockId="6.[144,272,167,191]" box="[144,272,167,191]" pageId="6" pageNumber="1914">
<emphasis box="[144,272,167,191]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="1914">Description</emphasis>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="6.[144,1104,207,295]" pageId="6" pageNumber="1914">
Male terminalia: epandrium strongly protruded ventrally (
<figureCitation box="[817,917,207,231]" captionStart="Figures 8–14" captionStartId="5.[212,289,1586,1608]" captionTargetBox="[212,1172,905,1543]" captionTargetId="figure-176@5.[212,1172,903,1544]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="Figures 8–14. Stegana (Steganina) jiajinshanensis sp. nov., Ƌ. (8) Epandrium (epan), surstylus (sur) and cercus (cerc) (lateral view); (9) surstylus (ventral view); (10) 10th sternite; (11, 12) hypandrium (hypd), parameres (pm), aedeagus (aed) and aedeagal apodeme (aed a) (ventral and lateral view); (13, 14) gonopods (ventral and lateral view). Scale bars: 0.1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5216814" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5216814/files/figure.png" pageId="6" pageNumber="1914">Figure 8</figureCitation>
). Surstylus with six prensisetae submedially (
<figureCitation box="[470,571,239,263]" captionStart="Figures 8–14" captionStartId="5.[212,289,1586,1608]" captionTargetBox="[212,1172,905,1543]" captionTargetId="figure-176@5.[212,1172,903,1544]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="Figures 8–14. Stegana (Steganina) jiajinshanensis sp. nov., Ƌ. (8) Epandrium (epan), surstylus (sur) and cercus (cerc) (lateral view); (9) surstylus (ventral view); (10) 10th sternite; (11, 12) hypandrium (hypd), parameres (pm), aedeagus (aed) and aedeagal apodeme (aed a) (ventral and lateral view); (13, 14) gonopods (ventral and lateral view). Scale bars: 0.1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5216814" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5216814/files/figure.png" pageId="6" pageNumber="1914">Figure 9</figureCitation>
). Paramere with ca. three sensilla (
<figureCitation captionStart="Figures 8–14" captionStartId="5.[212,289,1586,1608]" captionTargetBox="[212,1172,905,1543]" captionTargetId="figure-176@5.[212,1172,903,1544]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="Figures 8–14. Stegana (Steganina) jiajinshanensis sp. nov., Ƌ. (8) Epandrium (epan), surstylus (sur) and cercus (cerc) (lateral view); (9) surstylus (ventral view); (10) 10th sternite; (11, 12) hypandrium (hypd), parameres (pm), aedeagus (aed) and aedeagal apodeme (aed a) (ventral and lateral view); (13, 14) gonopods (ventral and lateral view). Scale bars: 0.1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5216814" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5216814/files/figure.png" pageId="6" pageNumber="1914">Figures 11, 12</figureCitation>
). Aedeagal opening nearly triangular in ventral view (
<figureCitation box="[780,892,271,295]" captionStart="Figures 8–14" captionStartId="5.[212,289,1586,1608]" captionTargetBox="[212,1172,905,1543]" captionTargetId="figure-176@5.[212,1172,903,1544]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="Figures 8–14. Stegana (Steganina) jiajinshanensis sp. nov., Ƌ. (8) Epandrium (epan), surstylus (sur) and cercus (cerc) (lateral view); (9) surstylus (ventral view); (10) 10th sternite; (11, 12) hypandrium (hypd), parameres (pm), aedeagus (aed) and aedeagal apodeme (aed a) (ventral and lateral view); (13, 14) gonopods (ventral and lateral view). Scale bars: 0.1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5216814" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5216814/files/figure.png" pageId="6" pageNumber="1914">Figure 11</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
